source: hand-authored
capture_date: 2026-07-05
updated: 2026-07-06 (#435, ISSUE_FILTER seam PR-A) — added `assignees` to
  both rows (iid 5 gets two, iid 3 gets none) so the same fixture also
  serves the widened itp_list_by_state/itp_list_forbidden_combos assignees
  assertions.
gitlab_version: 17.x
endpoint: GET /projects/:id/issues?state=opened&labels=autonomous&per_page=100
shape: array of issue objects (single page); .iid used as spec `number`; labels[] as name strings; assignees[] as {username} objects (normalized to username strings by the leaf); state ∈ opened|closed
notes: |
  Deliberately out of order (iid 5 before iid 3) — the leaf's normalize
  jq must sort ascending by number regardless of the server's natural
  order.
